> We love good Mexican Bean Stew with Tortilla Chips and this deliciously simple, chef-curated recipe doesn't disappoint. Time to bust out the pots and pans!

Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C.

Halve, peel and thinly slice the @red onion{1}(peeled and thinly sliced).

Halve the @bell pepper{2}(halved and sliced into thin strips) and discard the core and seeds.

Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a garlic press).

Trim the @spring onion{2}(trimmed and sliced thinly) then slice thinly.

Cut the @lime{1/2}(cut into wedges) into wedges.

Drain and rinse the @mixed beans{1 can}(drained and rinsed) in a #sieve{}.

Pop the peppers onto a #baking tray{}, drizzle with oil and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Toss to coat then spread out in a single layer.

Roast on the middle shelf of your oven until golden and soft, ~{15-17%minutes}.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of oil in a large #saucepan{} over medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the red onion and cook, stirring occasionally, until soft, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Add the garlic, @chipotle paste{2%tsp}, @smoked paprika{1%tsp} and @tomato puree{30%g} and cook, stirring, for ~{1%minute}.

> TIP: Add less chipotle paste if you don't like spice.

Add the @finely chopped tomatoes{1%can}(chopped) with the @vegetable stock powder{1%tsp} and a splash of water.

Season with salt and pepper, and a pinch of @sugar{pinch}.

Stir in the mixed beans.

Lower the heat and simmer until thickened, ~{8-10%minutes}. Stir occasionally.

While the stew cooks, make the tortilla chips!

Using some #scissors{}, cut each @super soft tortilla with whole wheat{2} into eight triangles.

> We used one tortilla per person but if you want to use two, that's fine - you have enough!

Place the chips on a baking tray and drizzle over some oil.

Season with salt and pepper, then spread them out in a single layer.

Bake on the top shelf of your oven until golden, ~{4-5%minutes}.

> TIP: Keep an eye on them to make sure they don't burn!

Once the peppers are roasted, add them to the stew and stir them through.

Add a splash of water to loosen if you need to.

Taste and season with salt and pepper.

Crumble the @feta cheese{50%g} into small pieces.

Divide the stew between #bowls{} and top with the feta and sliced spring onion.

Serve with lime wedges for squeezing over and tortilla chips alongside for dipping. Enjoy!